utils

Class RandomGraphMaker3

  • java.lang.Object
    • utils.RandomGraphMaker3

  • public class RandomGraphMaker3
extends java.lang.Object
    builds a random graph $G_{|V|,p}, given the number of nodes and the probability of any edge (i,j) existing in the graph (and optionally of course, the random seed). The graph may also have random weights on its nodes if the appropriate flag is set.

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
        invoke as: java -cp <classpath> utils.RandomGraphMaker3 <numnodes> <edgeProbability> <filename> [rndseed] [nodeweightsvariance]. If the nodeweightsvariance option is set to some positive number then the graph will have weights assigned to its nodes that will be random numbers drawn from the gaussian distribution, with mean equal to the node degree, and variance the specified value. If this option is used and set to some negative value, then the absolute value of this value will form the upper limit of the uniform distribution from which node weights will be drawn; if the value is integer, then the distribution used will be the discrete uniform distribution, else the continuous uniform distribution. If the option is not used, then every node will have weight equal to 1.0.
        Parameters:
        args - String[]
